title: Musical Exploration in Ireland and Scotland
content: Musical Exploration of Ireland and Scotland: It’s a trip of wild beauty, city bustle, historic icons – and 3 group performances! Start with Dublin’s St. Patrick Cathedral and Trinity’s Book of Kells. Ferry to Alloway and the port of Oban in Scotland’s Argyll area. Next, the isle of Iona, burial site of Scottish kings. Catch the Wallace Monument in medieval Stirling. Finish your tour in Edinburgh—a beautiful center for the arts.

title: Middle School Honors Performance Series at Carnegie Hall
content:
The Middle School Honors Performance Series at Carnegie Hall challenges elite students to perform at their very best. Students rehearse and perform under master conductors and have the opportunity to perform before invited representatives from collegiate and professional music programs. Though much of the students time is focused on performance preparation, the week also allows students to experience the best of the sights and the performance arts in New York City.

Learn More

title: Classical Highlights & Aegean Cruise
content: Is there a better way to experience the island allure of the Aegean Sea than aboard a cruise? Prepare to be swept away by the unparalleled beauty and enchanting waters that surround Greece, Turkey, and Crete as you visit the top sights and perform in three locations – Mycenae & Corinth, Rhodes, and Athens. From ruins to realizations, trace the story of modern man on your 9 day tour of classical highlights and Aegean cruise.

title: Music of Northern Italy
content: Feel the magical allure of inspiration as your ensemble performs music in northern Italy and Rome. With an itinerary that features world-class sites – including the Roman Amphitheater, St. Mark’s Basilica, The Grand Canal, The Duomo, The Ponte Vecchio, remains of the Roman Empire, and much more – and performances in Venice, Florence, and Rome, your 11 day tour delivers a classic view of this remarkable part of the world.

title: Rome to Salzburg
content: Your journey from Rome to Salzburg is a tour of early civilization’s greatest city to the heart of the Renaissance and includes the home of one of the world’s most celebrated composers – Mozart. Your 12 day trip delivers enduring inspiration and incredible passion for the beauty of life – and music – including the ruins and holy landmarks of Rome, and abundant sights in Pisa, Cinque Terra, Venice, Munich, and more. Your performances cities are Rome, Florence, and Salzburg.

title: Exploring Ancient Greece
content: Exploring ancient Greece is to review the foundations of modern life, from mythology to political, scientific, and social standards adopted by countless countries across the globe. You’ll perform in three cities – Mycenae, Olympia, and Athens – taking in the vibrant scenery and mammoth-sized influence of Greek culture along the way. Your 9 day tour also includes visits to Eleusis, Nafplio, Delphi, and Cape Sounion.

title: An Athenian Prelude
content: Your Athenian prelude includes three concert performances in Athens, and your entire 9 day tour showcases the everlasting influence of Greek culture and mythology. Set your sights on Temple of Poseidon, The Acropolis, Temple of Olympian Zeus, and Museum of Popular Greek Instruments, as well as day trips to Mycenae & Corinth and Delphi. Feel centuries of history around you as you make your contribution of expression through performance.

title: Paris & Madrid
content: Paris & Madrid – two cities that hardly need an introduction. Start in The City of Light, where you’ll also perform, for tours that include revolution, art, architecture, and decadence. Move on to Madrid for your second performance and savor the royal display and bustling metropolis of Spain’s capitol, then move to Toledo for your third and final performance.
